        "Sibling code in `goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` checks publish errors and logs warnings, creating inconsistent failure behavior for similar transition paths."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define one transition emission policy and apply it everywhere: either propagate publish errors for user-facing operations, or explicitly downgrade them to warnings via a shared helper that logs and tags dropped events. Replace direct fire-and-forget publish calls with that helper across new-ship and backup paths.",
