      "summary": "Multiple modules stringify errors instead of wrapping, breaking causal chains and `errors.Is/As` behavior.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/config/urbit.go",
        "goseg/handler/ship/backup.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/newship.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/config/urbit.go` uses `%v` when adding context in several returns (for example load/decode/persist helpers), which drops unwrap semantics.",
        "`goseg/handler/ship/backup.go` converts composed text to errors with `fmt.Errorf(\"%s\", text)` in multiple handlers, severing source causes.",
        "`goseg/shipworkflow/newship.go` returns `fmt.Errorf(\"%s\", errmsg)` from cleanup path even when `errmsg` was built from an underlying error."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Standardize on wrapped propagation (`%w`) whenever an underlying error exists, and only create string-only errors for true validation/user-message cases. Introduce helper constructors for user-display events versus internal wrapped errors to prevent accidental cause stripping.",
