      "suggestion": "Define explicit async error contracts for long-running workflows (e.g., completion channel/result future, or mandatory event-ack path) and keep synchronous handlers either blocking until critical phases succeed or returning a typed 'accepted/pending' result. Apply one contract consistently across new-ship and subsystem starters.",
